>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Comparison of SE and IR</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SE sequences are less sensitive to magnetic field inhomogeneities, magnetic susceptibilities, and generally give <u>high SNR and CNR</u>. The downsides are the <u>relatively long TR</u>（感觉只有一点点） and <u>corresponding long acquisition times</u>.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Gradient Echo</h4>\r\n<p><u><em>*</em>discussion below basd on SE***</u></p>\r\n<p>The GE technique uses a magnetic field gradient applied in one direction and then reversed to induce the formation of an echo, <u>instead of the 180-degree inversion pulse</u>.</p>\r\n<p>The GE is not a true SE but a purposeful <u>dephasing</u> and rephasing of the FID, it enhance the external megnetic inhomogeneities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The effect of flip angle:</p>\r\n<ol start=\'\' >\r\n<li><p>use anger much less than 60 degrees more than 90 degrees</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><p>because in the realm of <u>very short TR</u>, smaller flip angles require less time and create more transverse magnetization compared to larger flip angles.</p>\r\n<center><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YIjieYuan/typora-figurebed/master/img/20191025040910.png\" style=\"zoom:50%;\"></center>\r\n<center>Fig15| Why use small flip anger more</center>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p>Gradient Echo Sequences with Long TR</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TR greater than <u>200 ms</u>, flip angles greater than 45 degrees</li>\r\n<li>image contrast that is based on T2* rather than T2, because external magnetic field inhomogeneities are not cancelled.</li>\r\n<li>A relatively long TE tends to emphasize the differences between T2* and T2, rather than improve T2 contrast, as would be expected in an SE sequence.</li>\r\n<li>In most situations, however, GE imaging is not useful with long TR, except when contrast produced by magnetic susceptibility differences is desired.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote><p>GE并没有消除磁场不均匀导致的T2*衰减的影响，而是利用快速的、人造的dephase和rephase来在<u>短时间的TE</u>内完成测量，所以并不需要很大的TR就可以获得足够的信号强度。如果增大TR时间（TR影响<span class=\"MathJax_SVG\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;\"><svg xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" width=\"3.254ex\" height=\"2.439ex\" viewBox=\"0 -806.8 1400.9 1050.2\" role=\"img\" focusable=\"false\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.565ex;\"><defs><path stroke-width=\"0\" id=\"E144-MJMATHI-4D\" d=\"M289 629Q289 635 232 637Q208 637 201 638T194 648Q194 649 196 659Q197 662 198 666T199 671T201 676T203 679T207 681T212 683T220 683T232 684Q238 684 262 684T307 683Q386 683 398 683T414 678Q415 674 451 396L487 117L510 154Q534 190 574 254T662 394Q837 673 839 675Q840 676 842 678T846 681L852 683H948Q965 683 988 683T1017 684Q1051 684 1051 673Q1051 668 1048 656T1045 643Q1041 637 1008 637Q968 636 957 634T939 623Q936 618 867 340T797 59Q797 55 798 54T805 50T822 48T855 46H886Q892 37 892 35Q892 19 885 5Q880 0 869 0Q864 0 828 1T736 2Q675 2 644 2T609 1Q592 1 592 11Q592 13 594 25Q598 41 602 43T625 46Q652 46 685 49Q699 52 704 61Q706 65 742 207T813 490T848 631L654 322Q458 10 453 5Q451 4 449 3Q444 0 433 0Q418 0 415 7Q413 11 374 317L335 624L267 354Q200 88 200 79Q206 46 272 46H282Q288 41 289 37T286 19Q282 3 278 1Q274 0 267 0Q265 0 255 0T221 1T157 2Q127 2 95 1T58 0Q43 0 39 2T35 11Q35 13 38 25T43 40Q45 46 65 46Q135 46 154 86Q158 92 223 354T289 629Z\"></path><path stroke-width=\"0\" id=\"E144-MJMATHI-7A\" d=\"M347 338Q337 338 294 349T231 360Q211 360 197 356T174 346T162 335T155 324L153 320Q150 317 138 317Q117 317 117 325Q117 330 120 339Q133 378 163 406T229 440Q241 442 246 442Q271 442 291 425T329 392T367 375Q389 375 411 408T434 441Q435 442 449 442H462Q468 436 468 434Q468 430 463 420T449 399T432 377T418 358L411 349Q368 298 275 214T160 106L148 94L163 93Q185 93 227 82T290 71Q328 71 360 90T402 140Q406 149 409 151T424 153Q443 153 443 143Q443 138 442 134Q425 72 376 31T278 -11Q252 -11 232 6T193 40T155 57Q111 57 76 -3Q70 -11 59 -11H54H41Q35 -5 35 -2Q35 13 93 84Q132 129 225 214T340 322Q352 338 347 338Z\"></path></defs><g stroke=\"currentColor\" fill=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"0\" transform=\"matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)\"><use xlink:href=\"#E144-MJMATHI-4D\" x=\"0\" y=\"0\"></use><use transform=\"scale(0.707)\" xlink:href=\"#E144-MJMATHI-7A\" x=\"1371\" y=\"-213\"></use></g></svg></span><script type=\"math/tex\">M_z</script>的恢复程度），那么T1的对比度减少，<u>相当于是T2 weighting</u> ，那么不同于SE，这个时候如果的对比度来源是T2*。如果TE的时间更长，GE和SE所展现出来的对比度就会差别很大，究其原因，还是因为GE在T2和T2*的基础上又加上了一个人造的衰减和恢复。</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p>Gradient Echo Sequences with short TR</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p>TR less than <u>50 ms</u>, flip angles greater than 45 degrees</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><p>a steady-state equilibrium of longitudinal and transverse magnetization from pulse to pulse exists.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><p>Combination of multiple signal</p>\r\n<ol start=\'\' >\r\n<li><p>the FID signal generated at the end of the current RF pulse, and once rephased, contains T2* or T1 information depending on the TE</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>新的那个</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote><p>每一次pulse都对应一次测量，测量时间为nTR+​TE，TR is fixed, TE will depends weather it&#39;s T1 weighting or T2(T2*) weighting</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><p>a stimulated echo generated from the previous RF pulse acting on the persistent transverse magnetization accruing from the RF pulse <u>twice displaced</u>. The stimulated echo contains T2 and T2* weighting.</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>老的那个</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote><p>这里的T2和T2* weighting的意思应该是因为对于剩余信号而言TE‘很长（TE’=nTR+TE）</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p>Coherent GE</p>\r\n<center><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YIjieYuan/typora-figurebed/master/img/20191025040741.png\" style=\"zoom: 50%;\"></center>\r\n<center>Fig16| Coherent GE</center>\r\n<p>produce tissue contrast dependent on flip angle, TR, and TE.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>With moderate flip angles of 30 to 60 degrees, the differences in tissue contrast are primarily based upon T2/T1 ratios.Since most tissues with a long T2 also have a long T1 and vice versa, there is very little tissue contrast generated. So, This technique enhances vascular contrast, from which MR angiography sequences can be reconstructed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p>Incoherent, “Spoiled” Gradient Echo Techniques</p>\r\n<p>To achieve T1 weighting in short TR</p>\r\n<center><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YIjieYuan/typora-figurebed/master/img/20191025040939.png\" style=\"zoom:50%;\"></center>\r\n<center>Fig17| Incoherent(spoiled) GE acquisition</center>\r\n<p>adding a phase shift to successive RF pulses during the excitation of protons. Both the RF transmitter and RF receiver are phase locked, so that the receiver discriminates the phase of the GE from the SE generated by the previous RF pulse, now out of phase. Mostly, T1-weighted contrast is obtained, with <u>short TR</u>, <u>short TE</u>, and <u>moderate to large flip angle</u>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><p>Steady-State Free Precession</p>\r\n<center><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YIjieYuan/typora-figurebed/master/img/20191025041020.png\" style=\"zoom:50%;\"></center>\r\n<center>Fig18| Steady-state Free Precession(SSFP)</center>\r\n<p>SSFP sequences provide true T2 contrast weighting, are useful for brain and joint imaging, and can be used with three-dimensional volumetric acquisitions</p>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Summary:</p>\r\n<p>Coherent GE uses the combined FID and SE signals and produces contrast mainly depending on the ratio of T2/T1 or T2*/T1;</p>\r\n<p>Incoherent (or spoiled) GE produces contrast mainly based on T1 </p>\r\n<p>SSFP samples the SE signal only, thus producing signals that are more T2 weighted.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>12.6 MR Signal Localization</h3>\r\n<h4>Magnetic Field Gradients</h4>\r\n<div contenteditable=\"false\" spellcheck=\"false\" class=\"mathjax-block md-end-block md-math-block md-rawblock\" id=\"mathjax-n388\" cid=\"n388\" mdtype=\"math_block\">\r\n			\r\n		<div class=\"md-rawblock-container md-math-container\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div class=\"MathJax_SVG_Display\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"MathJax_SVG\" id=\"MathJax-Element-12-Frame\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;\"><svg xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" width=\"33.139ex\" height=\"4.79ex\" viewBox=\"0 -1279.5 14268 2062.1\" role=\"img\" focusable=\"false\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.818ex; max-width: 100%;\"><defs><path stroke-width=\"0\" id=\"E12-MJMATHI-4E\" d=\"M234 637Q231 637 226 637Q201 637 196 638T191 649Q191 676 202 682Q204 683 299 683Q376 683 387 683T401 677Q612 181 616 168L670 381Q723 592 723 606Q723 633 659 637Q635 637 635 648Q635 650 637 660Q641 676 643 679T653 683Q656 683 684 682T767 680Q817 680 843 681T873 682Q888 682 888 672Q888 650 880 642Q878 637 858 637Q787 633 769 597L620 7Q618 0 599 0Q585 0 582 2Q579 5 453 305L326 604L261 344Q196 88 196 79Q201 46 268 46H278Q284 41 284 38T282 19Q278 6 272 0H259Q228 2 151 2Q123 2 100 2T63 2T46 1Q31 1 31 10Q31 14 34 26T39 40Q41 46 62 46Q130 49 150 85Q154 91 221 362L289 634Q287 635 234 637Z\"></path><path stroke-width=\"0\" id=\"E12-MJMATHI-65\" d=\"M39 168Q39 225 58 272T107 350T174 402T244 433T307 442H310Q355 442 388 420T421 355Q421 265 310 237Q261 224 176 223Q139 223 138 221Q138 219 132 186T125 128Q125 81 146 54T209 26T302 45T394 111Q403 121 406 121Q410 121 419 112T429 98T420 82T390 55T344 24T281 -1T205 -11Q126 -11 83 42T39 168ZM373 353Q367 405 305 405Q272 405 244 391T199 357T170 316T154 280T149 261Q149 260 169 260Q282 260 327 284T373 353Z\"></path><path stroke-width=\"0\" id=\"E12-MJMATHI-74\" d=\"M26 385Q19 392 19 395Q19 399 22 411T27 425Q29 430 36 430T87 431H140L159 511Q162 522 166 540T173 566T179 586T187 603T197 615T211 624T229 626Q247 625 254 615T261 596Q261 589 252 549T232 470L222 433Q222 431 272 431H323Q330 424 330 420Q330 398 317 385H